About me:
I am obsessed with everything new.
I love technology and I also love programming.
I love sports.

Hi everyone, this is my real profile! This site is based on Google Sites and has now been moved to a domestic server in China. Never worry about the inaccessibility of chinese users! In fact, in early 2014, I had the idea of making a website myself, but I always felt that making a website is a very complicated thing that I cant learn it in a short time, and I am procrastinating! So it is delayed until the summer of 2019. If you ask me what really motivates me to make a website, it is actually a failure of resume delivery. In the summer of 2019, my resume did not pass the byte-dance resume screening. As a result, I did not have the opportunity to follow up on the computer-based test and the interviews, which prompted me to gradually create and improve my website and resume. There is another episode here. I didnt know until the re-delivery in 2020 that I didnt pass the resume screening one year ago because the time between my dual degree and the master s degree conflicted... However, The website is so staggered. In the previous first version of the site, I put my resume and blog together, which made the site look messy. Now, I decided to make a decent homepage, and move all the interfaces to this homepage, so that everyone can view the blog and that make the homepage much more impressive.


About me:

My name is Wu Zijian. I am currently studying for an engineer degree at the University of Paris XI in Paris, France. And I am studying for a dual master's degree at the University of Paris Saclay. I've been in photography since high school, and it's been eight years now. I really enjoy traveling with DSLRs and exploring new landscapes. I have been to 16 countries so far. The picture at the beginning of this article was taken at Iceland's Warnerdals volcano. Every trip brings me new feelings, and I am happy to share with you.

I am obsessed with everything new.

Others may worry that it is difficult for them to accept new things. This does not exist to me! If one day I discover an area I don't know, I will definitely rush forward to find out. I'm almost always the first to know about the major events in the technology circle, such as which company has launched what new product lines, what new breakthroughs have been made in extreme ultraviolet lithography, and which new ones have been launched by DxoMark. Machine evaluation and so on.

In July 2014, my parents bought me the first computer that belongs to me. At that time, the operating system was still Windows 8.1. I boldly predicted that computers without touch screens would be gradually phased out in the future. However, in October 2014, I became the first user to experience Windows 10. At that time, Windows 10 did not support the Chinese version of Cortana, and the Modern interface only supported a few programs. But I was suddenly attracted by the new interaction logic. For the first time, I found that the keyboard and mouse can be operated in the Modern interface. Since then, Windows 10 has become my main operating system. After that, I tried many versions of Linux and even experienced ZTE's new fulcrum. I also found that Linux is friendly to programmers. The open-source system allows me to do whatever I want, but I still cannot give up my love for Windows 10.

On June 4, 2019, the first beta of Developer Beta for iOS 13.0 and iPad OS was officially released, and I was fortunate to be the first batch of beta users. Although there are many bugs, I still cannot change my inner excitement and expectations for the new system. I can't help but bemoaned in the circle of friends that the iPad will replace the MacBook and become a productivity tool!

I love technology and I also love programming.

I have also been exposed to a lot of programming software and programming development in many fields. Limited to my major, I did not develop many hobbies in other fields, but focused on software programming exercises. Today, there are more than ten projects I have done, some of which have been open sourced on GitHub to prepare for future use, and some are not developed independently by me. After obtaining the consent of other students in the future Will gradually open source.

I love sports.

I started playing badminton in high school, and achieved good results in table tennis when I was undergraduate. Now living abroad, I have less and less time to play with good friends. I also gradually integrated into the life of my French classmates and started to go to the gym regularly to play with the iron. Good health is the capital of revolution! Of course, muscle shaping is also part of the purpose haha!

For more personal information, please see the "Resume" tab at the top of the homepage.
